===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|女|方|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}}. 方 also once bore the now-obsolete meaning of "take up" (space), which can explain the meaning of this character as being "to obstruct someone from approaching a woman".

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-p(j)aŋ|t=to block, obstruct}}; compare {{cog|my|ပင်း|t=to wedge, block}}, as well as the following Sinitic words (STEDT):
* {{och-l|坊|dike}}
* {{och-l|防|to protect against}}.

